FT  25 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Baillie Gifford Technology down
Baillie Gifford Technology announced a fall in net asset value per share
from 11.5p to 7.3p, as a result of a write-down in the value of its
investment in Intelligent Environments, a software company.
The trust is winding itself down by selling off its holdings and
redistributing the proceeds to investors. Intelligent Environments is one of
the few remaining assets.
Net losses for the six months to August 31 were Pounds 16,859 (profits of
Pounds 36,220), equivalent to 0.15p (earnings of 0.33p) per share. No
interim dividend is declared.
